President Obama called President Saleh of Yemen to commend him for the reform measures he announced and emphasized the need for concrete actions. Obama urged Yemeni security forces to show restraint and avoid violence against demonstrators exercising their rights. He also stressed the importance of Yemen taking strong action against Al Qaida in the Arabian Peninsula (AQAP) to protect lives both in Yemen and abroad. President Obama expressed concern about the release of Abd-Ilah al-Shai, who was associated with AQAP. President Saleh thanked Obama for U.S. support and pledged to strengthen relations with the United States.